{
  "doc_id": "770",
  "text": "We selected 20 SNPs from the IL10 gene region covering 23 250 bp (chr1:203,320,846-203,344,096) from the HapMap database release #21 (www.hapmap.org) using the Yoruba in Ibadan, Nigeria (Yoruba) data. The Haploview's program Tagger [CITATION_1] was used to derive a set of tag SNPs from the whole gene region such that each common SNP ($5%) in that set was captured with r2$0.8. Besides the SNPs obtained through this approach, polymorphisms that have been associated with a phenotype were included to the analyses. All SNPs were genotyped using mass spectrometry (Sequenom Inc, San Diego, CA, USA), according to the manufacturer's instructions.",
